                <p><label type="entry">XYSTUS</label>, among the Greeks, was a long portico, open or
                    covered at the top, where the athlete practised wrestling and running. The
                    gladiators who practised in it were called <hi rend="italic">xystici.</hi> Among
                    the Romans, the xystus was only an alley, or double row of trees, meeting like
                    an arbour, and forming a shade to walk under.</p>
            </div>
